com.hazelcast.spi.impl.operationservice.impl

Class InboundResponseHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.hazelcast.spi.impl.operationservice.impl.InboundResponseHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Consumer<Packet>

    public final class InboundResponseHandler
extends Object
implements Consumer<Packet>
    Responsible for handling responses for invocations. Based on the content of the response packet, it will lookup the Invocation from the InvocationRegistry and notify the Invocation. InboundResponseHandlers are not thread-safe. So if there are multiple threads processing responses, each thread needs to get its own instance. Only the backup handling is thread-safe since backups can be completed locally by any thread.
